A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Paul Zucca; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Paul Zucca on October 31, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Paul Zucca was a dedicated advocate for Grant Park and Southeast Atlanta who
5 served on numerous committees, boards, and organizations at the city, county, and state
6 levels to improve the community; and
7 WHEREAS, after moving from Midtown, he served as president of the Grant Park
8 Neighborhood Association and later as chairman of Neighborhood Planning Unit-W, helping
9 to strengthen bonds among East Atlanta, SAND, and Grant Park while securing resources
10 to support local growth; and
11 WHEREAS, he was an early supporter of the Neighborhood Charter School and the Atlanta
12 Charter Middle School before their merger, believing that all children deserved access to
13 quality education; and
